nce","The full A-B-C counter-move \u2014 what CP navigates."],["Impulse","A 5-wave motive structure that obeys the cardinal rules."],["Retracement / Pullback","The whole corrective move against the trend / one small step inside a move."],["FVG (imbalance)","A window left by a fast candle that price tends to return to fill."],["Origin / Order block","The last quiet candle before a strong move; price often returns to it."],["Deep zone","The .618\u20131.0 region where corrections usually finish."],["Confluence","Two or more independent reasons stacking at one level."],["Displacement","A decisive candle closing clean through a level."],["Spread","Ask \u2212 bid. Paid once per round trip."],["R (risk unit)","Entry-to-stop distance; targets are measured in multiples of R."]],a=[['A level is "broken" when\u2026',"A candle CLOSES beyond it \u2014 not when a wick merely pierces it."],["Price drives below a shelf of equal lows, then snaps back up. That was\u2026","A liquidity sweep \u2014 the stop-raid before the real move, not a breakout to chase."],["The 50/100/200 EMAs are stacked in order. That tells you\u2026","The trend is real (OP). Knotted, overlapping EMAs would say correction (CP)."],["A correction has only retraced .382 of the prior leg. Is it complete?","Treat it as unfinished \u2014 corrections reach at least .5 about 85% of the time; expect the .618\u20131.0 deep zone."]],o={padding:"26px",marginBottom:22},r={fontSize:12,color:e.sage,letterSpacing:".08em",textTransform:"uppercase",marginBottom:8};return React.createElement("section",{style:{maxWidth:980,margin:"0 auto",padding:"72px 28px"}},React.createElement("p",{className:"h-sans",style:{letterSpacing:".18em",textTransform:"uppercase",fontSize:12,color:e.oxblood,margin:"0 0 12px"}},"Resources"),React.createElement("h1",{style:{fontWeight:700,fontSize:40,margin:"0 0 14px"}},"Open to everyone"),React.createElement("p",{style:{fontSize:18,lineHeight:1.6,maxWidth:"64ch",marginBottom:36}},"Free by design \u2014 a 